<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
This new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wang, Wang, Zhou &amp; Dai" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Idioscopus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Idioscopus furcaprocessus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="furcaprocessus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Idioscopus furcaprocessus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in general appearance, including having a yellow patch on the forewing clavus. The sinuate shaft of the aedeagus in lateral view is similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. confuscous" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="confuscous">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. confuscous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pruthi) (see Viraktamath, 1980: fig. 15), 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. bihamulus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="bihamulus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. bihamulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. recurvatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="recurvatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. recurvatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName genus="I." lsidName="I. nitellicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="97" rank="species" species="nitellicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">I. nitellicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it differs from these and other species in having an unpaired, ventral, spine-like process proximad of the midlength of the shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Coloration</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
General color reddish brown. Crown yellowish with darker reddish-brown markings; eyes yellowish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2A-C</figureCitation>
). Pronotum and mesonotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2A</figureCitation>
) reddish brown, mesonotum paler with yellowish hue. Face (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2B</figureCitation>
) greenish yellow with frontoclypeus and anteclypeus pale reddish brown; male antennae with apical disc, black. Mesepimeron (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2C</figureCitation>
) with black patch. Forewing clavus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2A</figureCitation>
) with large, lemon-yellow patch bordered with dark reddish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
External features as in generic description with head and thorax shagreen; male antennae with apical disc (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2A-C</figureCitation>
); forewing (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2D</figureCitation>
) with two subapical cells, inner subapical open.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Male genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male pygofer (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2E, F</figureCitation>
) conically rounded apically, without ventral process; anal collar thin, upturned apically; dorsoanterior apodemes well developed. Anal tube (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2E</figureCitation>
) long. Subgenital plates (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2E</figureCitation>
) broader in distal one-third in lateral view, longer than pygofer, sharply upturned in basal third, with long hair-like marginal setae distally. Connective (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2G</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped, broad, with short stem. Style apophysis (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2G</figureCitation>
) narrowed to apex with weakly serrated inner margin. Aedeagus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. male A habitus, dorsal view B face C head and thorax, lateral view D forewing E genital capsule, lateral view F pygofer dorsal view G connective and style, dorsal view H aedeagus, lateral view I aedeagus ventral view. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671693" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">2H, I</figureCitation>
) with shaft laterally compressed, broad in basal half then narrowed and slightly sinuate distally to acute apex in lateral view, with one pair of subapical bifid processes, each fork unequal, an unpaired ventral spine-like process proximad of midlength; dorsal apodeme laterally compressed, distally expanded in lateral view and laterally expanded distally in ventral view.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Female genitalia</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Posterior margin of sternite VII (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Ovipositor. Female. A-E Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. F-J Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. A, F sternite VII B, G first valvula C, H apex of first valvula D, I second valvula E, J apex of second valvula." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671694" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">3F</figureCitation>
) slightly produced medially. Valvulae as in Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Ovipositor. Female. A-E Idioscopus bihamulus sp. nov. F-J Idioscopus ventrispinus sp. nov. A, F sternite VII B, G first valvula C, H apex of first valvula D, I second valvula E, J apex of second valvula." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1095.76731.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/671694" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">3G-J</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Measurements (mm).</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Male: body length including tegmina 4.50-4.95. Medial length of crown 0.18-0.22, width 1.55-1.60. Distance from ocellus to eyes 0.15-0.20. Medial length of pronotum 0.45-0.48, width 1.35-1.45; scutellum length 0.50-0.55, width 0.65-0.70. Female: body length 4.60-5.20 including tegmina.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="97" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="97">
The new species name is derived from the words 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">ventri</emphasis>
- and 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="97">spinus</emphasis>
, referring to the ventral spine-like process of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
